title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 10mm Model 1076
postcontent:
I am selling my Smith & Wesson 10mm model 1076. This is the model that was issued to the FBI in the mid 90's. It has all the FBI model specifications. This gun is a beast--very powerful! It is a "man's" gun and I would not recommend it for a woman's hand. Great stopping power for home defense or hunting sidearm. Capable of taking down a black bear! Relatively new condition considering only 150 rounds were shot thru it. It was kept in the house as a home defense weapon (which is why it was hardly shot) and passed down to me by my father. He put 100 rounds thru it and I have put only 50 thru. No malfunctions at all between the two of us. This gun has been very well cared for...cleaned and lubricated after every use. Very solid weapon and best 10mm I have ever shot. Trigger reset is very minimal and gun is very accurate. I am only selling it because I want an XDM .45 Compact and my wife said i have to sell one of my guns First or i can't get it (lol) so I priced it to sell fast. This is a steal for one of the best 10mm ever made. This model is no longer produced and probably harder to come by than most. FBI issued models have been sold for $2000+ on auction sites (no lie look it up!). This may or may not be an FBI issued weapon but has all the same specifications as the FBI issue from what I have read. I haven't checked with S&W (didn't care enough to) but you could call them with the serial number if you wanted to find out. FBI issued 1076 are worth the premium price but regardless of what mine is I am selling it for $650!! Here are a couple links if you want to read up on this gun's history and info- http://www.chuckhawks.com/s-w_1076_pistol.htm

title: For Sale/Trade:  Ruger SR9C Stainless
postcontent:
Like new condition SR9C purchased new in August 2011.  Comes with all of the goodies (case, 17 rd mag, 10 rd mag, loader and original purchase receipt).  Estimate 50-100 rounds through it (not broken in yet).

The SR9c compact pistol weighs in at 23.40 oz. and features an overall length of 6.85", a height of 4.61", and the same slim 1.27" grip width (across safety levers) as the full-sized SR9. It comes with two magazines that provide options in both capacity and grip size. The standard magazine holds 10 rounds and features a flat bottom butt plate; a finger grip extension floor plate is also included. The second magazine features a grip adapter and holds 17 rounds, instantly transforming the smaller, compact grip into a full-sized 9mm grip. The 3.50" barreled pistol features an integral accessory rail that accommodates most lights and lasers.

The SR9c compact pistol utilizes the same adjustable, high-visibility 3-Dot sight system as its full-sized predecessor, setting it apart from many compact pistols that rely on fixed sights. New serrations are located on the front portion of the slide, making it easier to both manipulate the slide and to press check the chamber. The SR9c is available with a glass-filled nylon frame and through-hardened slide in either a brushed stainless or blackened finish. State compliant variations are available where necessary and ship with two 10-round magazines.

Just like the original, full-sized SR9, the SR9c is loaded with modern safety features like a 1911-style ambidextrous manual safety, internal trigger bar interlock and striker blocker, trigger safety, magazine disconnect, plus a visual and tactile loaded chamber indicator.

Buyer must be legally permitted to own a firearm in Ohio (no firearm disabilities).  Email or text Five-One-Three 617-1295

title: For Sale:  Sog Specialty knife
postcontent:
This knife is in excellent condition and sold on eBay for 220 used in used condition my loss is your gain. Please email me and I will send you pictures SOG Knives Collectors' Review/Take:
The SOG Tomcatis one of the largest folding knives from SOG. It features athick blade of 0.2" and is backedup by a solid lock.This makes it a heavy-duty folding knife, and though it weighs more than the average folding knife it will stand up to hard use. It was also one of the first folding knives to incorporate a bowie knife design into a folding knife, along the lines of the S1 Bowie. The SOG Tomcat also won 'Overall Knife of the Year' award in 1988, oneof the first awards won by the company, for its greatand unique design. Many ownersparticularly like this version of the Tomcat for its clean look and heavy duty lock, like many of SOG's early folders.

The Tomcat was and still isa popular design and has not dropped off the SOG production list. It is one of the most collectible SOG folding knives and the earliest version of the SOG Tomcat is hard to find, with the right engravings. Other later versions include theTomcat (Cocobolo) - limited run withCocobolo wood handles,Tomcat II and the Tomcat 3.0.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Armalite AR10T with Barrel Work and Extras
postcontent:
I have this rifle that started life as an AR10T. It has the Armalite SS Match Barrel with a 1-11.25" twist. The barrel was originally 24" in length. I found the length a bit unnecessary and had Jim Burke in Southern Arizona chop it to 20" and thread it. It now sports a Vortex Flash suppressor. The original Armalite free-float tube has been replaced with an aluminum, smooth bottom unit that was created for the Army Marksmanship Unit by Superior Weapon Systems. The SWS tube has picatinny rails along the top and all four sides at the end of the tube. It's great for mounting bipods and slings forward. The lower has a Tango Down Battlegrip and still contains the 2-stage match trigger from Armalite. The long A2 stock has been replaced with a standard AR15 mil-spec carbine tube and a VLTOR EMOD stock. The EMOD stock has a nice cheek weld and "J" shape that aids in shooting off a bipod. In order to allow the use of standard AR15 carbine stocks, the buffer and spring has been replaced with a "XH" unit from Slash's Heavy Buffers which also aids in taming recoil. Everything in this rifle has been thought out to provide long range accuracy and the lightest weight / shortest length possible. 1 20 round magazine included. Bipod not included. I also have an Eberlestock Gunslinger in Flat Dark Earth is available for an additional $180.

This rifle has proven capable of .75-1MOA out to 600 yds with 168 gn HPBT SMKs. 600 is the longest range I've been able to fire it at. I am sure that it's capable of more. I no longer have that much range to shoot at, so I am content with my 16" AR10. This rifle has approximately 400 rounds through it.
